&gt;&gt; &gt; not 300m above us.&quot; he said. &quot;Something that massive falling from
&gt;&gt; &gt; orbit could easily explain the force of the water.&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;How&#39;s the rest of the city,&quot; asked Salveo.
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Not good. Most the people escaped to their shelters, however the
&gt;&gt; &gt; buildings were all destroyed. Except the tower and several on the far
&gt;&gt; &gt; side of the island.&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;The shuttles?&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Ours was destroyed, a few were in the air when the wave hit.&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;I dont think we can rebuild this.&quot; said Salveo after a moment of
&gt;&gt; &gt; looking at the devistation.
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;I think its possible, but unwise. I think this gives us a new
&gt;&gt; &gt; opportunity to rejoin our Maximal allies and pool our resources. So
&gt;&gt; &gt; for the moment, we should recover what we can and put it into the
&gt;&gt; &gt; shuttle, then assist Atlantis in anyway possible.&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Rejoin Lord Elder? Will that work? And what about Atlantis?&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Atlantis will be safe from the Unicronians; they wont bother with a
&gt;&gt; &gt; few hundred scientists and fisherman. What they want is to destroy
&gt;&gt; &gt; us, and they will follow us wherever we decide to have our base. As
&gt;&gt; &gt; for that crashed ship, I dont think its wise to mount a expedition
&gt;&gt; &gt; while the city lies in ruin and we remain baseless.&quot;
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Right, so priority one, help the city and recover what we can from
&gt;&gt; &gt; our base.&quot; replied Salveo.
&gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Correct.&quot;
